ce:section.ce:para:
The International Council for Harmonization (ICH) Q2 R2 guidelines were used to validate the response between PN@CDs and PAN [47]. The synthesized PN@CDs have an intrinsic dual emission with two emission bands at 355 nm and 425 nm after being excited at 300 nm. PN@CDs were found to have a double-off response in the presence of PAN quantitatively (Fig. 3
                        ). Firstly, to create the calibration plot, the F°/F at both emission bands separately (355 nm and 425 nm) were plotted versus the matching concentrations (µg/mL) of PAN. Upon applying the traditional non-ratiometric response (F°/F355) and (F°/F425), the determination coefficient (r2) value was found to be 0.9662 and 0.9706 respectively while the application of the ratiometric response (I425/I355) against the concentration of PAN (µg/mL), the r2 was increased to reach 0.9986 (Fig. 4
                        ). This novel ratiometric probe was found to have a considerable positive impact on the analytical response's linearity. I425/I355 was the analytical reaction that produced the best results, and it was used further. A good coefficient of determination was obtained in the concentration range of 0.50 – 35.00 µg/mL.
